{
  "texts": [
    "For sentence pairs with larger values of y i, x i and y i are closely aligned, while for sentence pairs with smaller values of y i, the difference between x i and y i becomes more pronounced.",
    "Conversely, larger values of D 1 encompass more semantic information, thereby intensifying the semantic distinctions among each sentence pair.",
    "The gap between x i and y i is amplified when y i is smaller.",
    "The PCC and MSE remain constant at D 1 = 20000 and D 1 = 25000.",
    "However, when the variable interval is reduced, changes occur in both PCC and MSE."
  ]
}